CaMKIIγ mRNA expression was up-regulated in the pAd-CaMKIIγ group and down-regulated in the pAd-shRNA group compared to normal cells (Fig. 5A). There were no differences between cells in the Normal and Empty vector groups. These data suggest that the generated pAd-CaMKIIγ and pAd-shRNA adenovirus vectors successfully over-expressed and inhibited CaMKIIγ mRNA expression. CaMKIIγ mRNA expression in cells treated with ropivacaine hydrochloride also increased significantly compared to cells not treated with ropivacaine hydrochloride.Figure 5
